1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,609
Success just naturally followed.

2
00:00:03,199 --> 00:00:08,609
Think for a moment about a club or a civic organization you know that is fading away.

3
00:00:08,959 --> 00:00:13,809
Chances are, all it needs is enthusiasm to bring it back to life.

4
00:00:14,639 --> 00:00:18,609
Results come in proportion to enthusiasm applied.

5
00:00:19,119 --> 00:00:23,250
Enthusiasm is simply, this is great, here's why.

6
00:00:23,839 --> 00:00:29,328
Here is a three-step procedure that will help you to develop the power of enthusiasm.

7
00:00:29,328 --> 00:00:31,568
1.

8
00:00:32,159 --> 00:00:33,568
Dig into it deeper.

9
00:00:34,079 --> 00:00:35,409
Make this little test.

10
00:00:35,919 --> 00:00:43,169
Think of two things in which you have little or no interest, maybe cards, certain kinds of music, a sport.

11
00:00:43,599 --> 00:00:48,208
Now ask yourself, how much do I really know about these things?

12
00:00:48,559 --> 00:00:52,688
Odds are 100 to 1 that your answer is not much.

13
00:00:53,439 --> 00:00:58,448
I confess that for years I had absolutely no interest in modern art.

14
00:00:58,639 --> 00:01:05,889
It was just so many botched up lines, until I let a friend who knows and loves modern art explain it to me.

15
00:01:06,159 --> 00:01:10,208
Really, now that I've dug into it, I find it fascinating.

16
00:01:10,879 --> 00:01:15,649
That exercise supplies one important key for building enthusiasm.

17
00:01:15,839 --> 00:01:21,328
To get enthusiastic, learn more about the thing you are not enthusiastic about.

18
00:01:22,079 --> 00:01:26,529
chances are you are quite unenthusiastic about bumblebees.

19
00:01:26,639 --> 00:01:32,208
But if you study bumblebees, find out what good they do, how they relate to other bees,

20
00:01:32,239 --> 00:01:35,088
how they reproduce, where they live in winter.

21
00:01:35,279 --> 00:01:42,609
If you find out all you can about bumblebees, you will soon find yourself really interested in bumblebees.

22
00:01:43,359 --> 00:01:49,328
To show trainees how enthusiasm can be developed through the dig-into-it-deeper technique,

23
00:01:49,599 --> 00:01:52,208
I sometimes use a greenhouse example.

24
00:01:52,399 --> 00:02:00,609
In a deliberately casual way, I ask the group, Are any of you interested in manufacturing and selling greenhouses?

25
00:02:00,959 --> 00:02:04,129
Not once have I gotten an affirmative answer.

26
00:02:04,399 --> 00:02:07,169
Then I make a few points about greenhouses.

27
00:02:07,439 --> 00:02:15,009
I remind the group how, as our standard of living rises, people become more and more interested in non-necessities.

28
00:02:15,439 --> 00:02:21,568
I suggest how much Mrs. America would enjoy growing her own orchids and orange blossoms.

29
00:02:21,839 --> 00:02:26,848
I point out that if tens of thousands of families can afford private swimming pools,

30
00:02:27,039 --> 00:02:32,609
millions could afford greenhouses, because greenhouses are relatively inexpensive.

31
00:02:33,119 --> 00:02:39,250
I show them that if you could sell a $600 greenhouse to only one family in 50,

